ok so i was real bored...bite me

ok i havent updated in a few days, i need to start with what happened sunday at the ass-crack of dawn. I was sleeping soundly, had been since 1:55am when i crashed. at 4:55 i was awoken by the sounds of banging on my door and my friend screaming "Jess get up!!!"...since i was half asleep i responded with a simple "hang on a minute" and rolled over. She then yelled again "Jess get up now, theres a fire" and all i can remember saying was "oh fuck". i jumped out of my bed and pulled a pair of pants on over my shorts...grabbed a hoodie, flipflops and my room key. i walked into the hallway holding my hoodie, and immediately had to cover my face because of the smoke in the hallway. i ran for the stairs and got out of the building. once we were outside my friend explained to me that there was a fire in the girls bathroom right across the hall from my dorm room. i definately think that was the scariest moment of my life. it was awful. they finally let all the students back into the building, but everyone form my floor had to wait in the 7th floor lounge for a while. By 6:15 i was climbing back into my nice warm bed. I slept until 2:30 that afternoon. stupid fires! If it werent for my friend though, i would never have woken up to the alarms. i was out cold and i had a towel at the base of the door to stop drafts. so i would never have smelled smoke either. yup, i would have become toast.

ok can someone please tell me why i cant sleep at night anymore? i just cant seem to sleep well. if anyone has a solution, please, be a dear and let me know!

peace

holy fuck! im home now! i drove down here last night with my 2 friends from school. we dropped one off with her boyfriend then my friend and i came here. i couldnt sleep i was so excited! my sister and i tackled eachother and fell on the ground. that kinda hurt. i was soooo happy to see her. everyone was up when i got home, and it so nice to see them. i sat in my room looking around and going through my scrapbook, i cant believe how much i missed this place. i went to my old high school today and visited a lot of teachers. they were all so happy to see me. and of course my shop teachers had to torment me. of all the places i said i would never go back to i went back to that god damn school. but i was reminded why i hated it so much. i had a little dirtball kid in one of the shop classes ask me what i was supposed to be for halloween. and i was like excuse me....but im not dressed up for halloween. stupid asshole. i hate kids. oh well. i left the school, picked up breakfast for myself, my dad and my friend. now im sitting in my living room, and it feels so nice to be here, with CNN on and drinking coffee with dad.....enough for now, peace

ok its official...everytime i hang out with my friend from friendster...we have fire alarms go off in this building the same day. dead serious. i hung out with him wednesday, 2 hours after he left we had a fire alarm. today, he dropped me off between 3 and 4 this morning, this afternoon we have another fire alarm. what the hell! seriously, its way too weird. hehe. its ok i like to hang out with him so i guess i just have to deal with it.

well nothing else to write about...just thought the fire drill thing was important. peace

well, last night was girls night out. 4 of us went out to fubar and played some pool, played the jukebox and then headed back to the dorms. we got changed real fast and then headed over to the zeta beta tau frat house, which isnt really a frat house its just some guys in the frat with an apartment together. we had a few beers and chilled there for a while, then we headed off to witch doctors for some dancing fun. it was awesome. my legs are real sore from dancing but its all good. i had a blast. my one friend got hit real hard by a shot so we ended up taking her back here and making sure she felt better before she went to bed. i finally went to sleep around 5am. my neighbor came and knocked on my door at 1 and woke me up. we went to Plate-Ohs for lunch with one of our other friends. We just got back and im going to give my friend a call and then maybe take a nap. i might be going home next weekend. my friend wants to go to NYC friday night, and he has a car. so he might take me home and stay at my place for the weekend. im excited, this time it looks like it actually may happen that i get to go home. well i have nothing else to write as of now, and im very sleepy..peace

well, last nite was really cool. i got to meet one of my friends from friendster...real cool guy, made me laugh a lot. another friend of mine said we made a "cute couple", i thought that was kinda nifty. we went to fubar with a few other people. i played pool against my friend and i beat her, then i played against my friend from online and won again, i was surprised i won though because i had 2 whiskey sours. normally when i drink i cant play pool for shit. we hung out at the bar for a while, played songs on the jukebox, i had a couple more drinks...as did everyone else for the most part. i got a complimentary shot which was soco and peach schnapps, it was soooo yummy. i got back to my room around 12 and changed, then went down to my friends room on the 3rd floor to hang out. came back up here around 1 and i was sitting online chatting with a few people. and around 130 the fire alarms went off, so i grabbed my slippers and woke up my roomie and her boyfriend and went outside. it was freezing cold and flurrying and everyone was out there in pajams with blankets wrapped around them and stuff. we didnt come back into the dorm until around 2am. it was sooo cold out. i was pissed off. i went to sleep a little while after that and woke up around 1130 this morning. 

i played hackey sack in the square outside the union again. it seems to be something i do every tuesday and wednesday during bengal paws. hung out with some friends for a while...they left and my other friend came up to visit. just got back from my awful dinner in the dining hall. it was hotdog and hamburger night, needless to say i had a salad. so now im sitting in my room, listening to some music and minding my own business...what fun. 

peace
